The Hot Access Tier is designed for data that is frequently accessed and requires low latency.

Characteristics:

* Higher storage cost
* Lower access cost
* Immediate availability

For example, a website serving images or videos to users stores content in the Hot tier.

A real-life use case is active application data such as user uploads and frequently accessed documents.

Another example is real-time analytics systems where data is continuously accessed.

Hot tier ensures fast performance for frequently used data.
